related_questions.question: Is it OK to eat mulberry?
related_questions.snippet: They're a wild berry with a wonderfully sweet flavor and are packed with antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals. Easy to prepare and eat, mulberries can be used in place of or alongside most other berries. They are also wonderful as a snack and sweet enough to replace treats that are typically loaded with added sugars.

related_questions.question: Is mulberry a fruit or blackberry?
related_questions.snippet: People tend think mulberries and blackberries are almost the same fruit. While they do look a bit alike, they are actually very different. In fact, mulberries are not even a berry. They are a fruit that grows on a deciduous tree, whereas blackberries are a true berry belonging to the rose botanical family.

related_questions.question: What is so special about a mulberry tree?
related_questions.snippet: Mulberry trees are low maintenance and require very little attention once they are established. They are also relatively resistant to pests and diseases, making them a great choice for land managers who want to attract wildlife without the added hassle of constantly maintaining their trees.

buttons.title: WHITE MULBERRY - Uses, Side Effects, and More - WebMD
buttons.snippet: Chemicals in white mulberry work similarly to some medicines used for type 2 diabetes. They slow the breakdown of sugar in the stomach so that it's absorbed more slowly into the blood. This helps the body keep blood sugar levels in a healthy range. People commonly use white mulberry for diabetes.
